Trust levels of apps launched from low rights IE sessions.The ElevationPolicy dictates how IE handles applications that want to executein other applications that reside outside of the Low Rights IE session.* AppName is the executable* AppPath is the directory* CLSID is used if it launches a COM server through CoCreateInstance* Policy (DWORD) is the trust level- of 0 through 3.* 3 Protected Mode silently launches the broker as a medium integrity process.* 2 Protected Mode prompts the user for permission to launch the process. If    permission is granted- the process is launched as a medium integrity process.* 1 Protected Mode silently launches the broker as a low integrity process.* 0 Protected Mode prevents the process from launching.
